>i'll look for both J and G switches... but where in the heck is the
>part # on the switch???

On the "Original VW Ersatzteile" box, probably.  :)  The J switch is
most likely for Buses with orange rear turn signals.  The brake light
wire doesn't go through the turn signal switch on it, and there are
fewer wires - the J switch has 5 wires, where the G switch has 8.

>i might start by resoldering the spare's ground wires on, but my skills
>at the iron ain't too hot.

Those just operate the headlight dimmer.  If you want, you can run the
wires from the body that connect to those wires to a separate momentary-
contact pushbutton on the dash somewhere.

>oh, one more thing - what size are the screws that hold the t/s
>switch in the housing, and the housing to the column? i se the
>bentley says m5, etc, but what pitch/thread?

Either check the parts manual or guess at a standard size.  Sort of like
if an older US car called for a 1/4" bolt, you'd try a 1/4-20 first.  For
M4 it's 0.7 mm and for M5 it's 0.8 mm.

Matt Roberds
